Sec. 71.047. EXPENSE OF TREATMENT. (a) The owner, manager, or
person in charge of the nursery product, florist item, or premises is
liable for all expenses of treatment or destruction under Section
71.046 of this code.
(b) The department or the county attorney of the county in
which the premises are located may sue to recover expenses under
Subsection (a) of this section. If successful, the department or
county attorney is entitled to an award of all costs of suit,
including attorney's fees.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1157, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

